properties.name: 16th Birthday, March '06.
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsMy Birthday party, it was all a bit embarressing and I vowed off drinking heavily since ;). My toilet cistern got broken, but it still managed to be fun. The costumes were "Social Stereotypes". Bring on the return of Chardonney.

properties.name: After Soho Picninc
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsLOLx4million at us walking down here and James coaxing Chris into holding his hand (for jokes).

properties.name: Alleyway
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsJames, Steph and I. Valentine\'s Day, 2006. We snapped ourselves down this tiny alley when we got lost (because of James, not me). We also saw the boy who plays Cedric Diggory that day, but we didn\'t get a photo of that.

properties.name: Brighton Pride '05
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsFancy Dress, James, Rhys, Sally, Naomi, Alcohol and Bad Food make for one hell of a party and one hell of a hang over. I fell down a hill and still have a scar, and we were caught on camera playing spin the bottle. We \'narf loved it.

properties.name: Chavving It Up, Summer '05.
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsJames, Jade, Sally - Dressing Up. I was a chav, James a skater, Jade a goth. It was super fun. My alter-ego, Chardonney, even got her own face-pic.

properties.name: Christmas Party, '05.
properties.description: Posted by Generalsmuts I am a party monster. Although more people came to this one, it was less riotous than my birthday. Odd. Fancy dress, as is usual.

properties.name: Cuckmere Haven
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsAs amazing geography students, we were required to go to this "Outstanding Place of Natural Beauty" in the cold and rain back in year 10. We met a little 3 year old chinese girl called Su-Lin who lived in a fishing cottage just falling over the edge of the cliff. She reminded me of the girl in The Ring. (& Alison Moulds fell down a rabbit hole, which is always funny). We all wore macintoshes like proper geeks.

properties.name: Dover Castle
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsI danced on top of this castle with my best friends in the rain, there was no one else about and it was fantastic!

properties.name: Ellie's 15th & 16th
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsApril 2005 = All colour photos. April 2006 = The photo of me dressed up a little strangely.

properties.name: Emerald's Summer Party
properties.description: Posted by Generalsmuts Summer \'05. Emerald\'s summer party. We all had to wear a dress and played super duper games.

properties.name: Gay Pride '05
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsVarious photos from the march from our vantage point on the Metro Bus! Yey!

properties.name: Gay Pride '05
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsWhere I discovered those slightly dubious ready-mixed Gin and Tonic drinks, with James and Sanaya.

properties.name: Hedingham Castle
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsYear 10 History Field Day, January \'05. This freezing cold day at a draughty castle sparked the game "How Many People Can You fit in a Guardrobe?" as a time-killer. Riveting.

properties.name: James' 16th!
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsI remember trying to eat dinner like a civilised person but Naomi and James ruining it because they were running around screaming and dancing to Rocky Horror.

properties.name: Keston Ponds
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsNaomi & I came here back in Summer 2004, which seems like forever ago. All that remains is this rather amsuing photograph.

properties.name: LAST year 9 disco.
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsThis one is a funny one. June 2004, so long ago! We\'ve all changed so much in 2 years. Alison has bright blonde hair and I haven\'t seen Joe is YEARS. Mostly I just like to lol at Peter and Joe in these. & Jess and her boyfriend shagging on the wall behind them. Ah, year 9.

properties.name: Last Day
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsSome classmates and I had a lovely picnic here after our last day of school, even though it was raining a bit. We struggled through! [June \'06]

properties.name: Mucking About
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsOwn Clothes Day + A Camera = Everyone goes a bit mad. October \'05.

properties.name: Natural History Museum
properties.description: Posted by Generalsmuts I\'ve been here many times, but the photos are from the time I went with Deepali and Rhys in January 2005. It\'s a place for us all to become little kids again.

properties.name: On the Trains
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsSteph and I rocked out on the train to James\'s place in may 2005. With James we went for a walk and then got locked out, but enjoyed it all the same.

properties.name: Performing Arts : Nightmare Before Christmas
properties.description: Posted by Generalsmuts Our last performing arts entry (end of year 9, 2004) was a 15 minute chopped up version of the Nightmare Before Christmas. It had it\'s downfalls (namely, a scene with Emerald as Jack "flying" in her sleigh), but overall, I loved it. I was Sandy Claws.

properties.name: Pride '05
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsWe all collapsed here after a long march, with the collection of people James and I had seemed to accumulate throughout the day. There was some Abba dancing after.

properties.name: Rhys Turns 16
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsWhen Rhys was 16 in July \'05 we went to Hastings and buried Matt Lofthouse in the sand. I also had to attatch Deepali\'s socks to a hand-dryer in a public loo so that they wouldn\'t be soaking wet from when she decided swimming in the sea with all her clothes on was a good idea.

properties.name: Rhys, the Jokester.
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsAfter Soho - Rhys sits on Steph. It just makes me laugh.

properties.name: Robot Wars.
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsLast Day of School (year 11, anyway) we dressed up in our homemade robot boxes and smashed into each other. [June 2006]

properties.name: SAP Meeting, Summer '05.
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsThe legendary SAP was formed here, which has evolved slightly this summer as Gayzzzzzz, with extra members. Rhys, James, Sally, Naomi meet up for post-Brighton pride picnic. Hilarity ensued.

properties.name: SAP Remembering.
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsThis brought up memories of SAP the year before. A mysterious sign outside Embankment for us to stare at. [May \'06]

properties.name: Soho Square Picnic
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsBuff sunny picnic with the gayzzzzzz gang. Early May, \'06. Pom-bears, tinny music through ipod speakers and dodgy ready-mixed gin and tonic. Perfect.

properties.name: Steph's Easter Party
properties.description: Posted by Generalsmuts A big old ho down in Steph\'s Attic Room, April 2006. The last big party we could manage before exams dragged us in. Somehow the teenage partying also included a Snoopy Puzzle.

properties.name: Steph's Party
properties.description: Posted by Generalsmuts March 2005. The first time I met James! So this was important. We both threw up, me on Steph\'s brother John and he in the bathroom. A mushroom from the pizza came up his nose. NICE! (He used to think I was mysterious and arty, now he just knows i\'m weird and spaced out). I like to think we\'ve grown up since then. We all know we haven\'t.

properties.name: Summer 2004.
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsSummer 2004! Me and Naomi being best buddies and the first time I ever really got a lot of photos taken of me. Discovering new technology huh?

properties.name: The Day Steph Ran Away
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsStephanie anbandoned James, John and I in this park (which has become close to my heart). She shouldn\'t of done it, because we took far too many photos of us being stupid. We also caught some people shagging in a bush. May or June \'05.

properties.name: The People at Pride
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsJames proceeded to have his photo taken with as many people at Pride \'05 as possible. [july]

properties.name: Tiny Little Party, '05.
properties.description: Posted by Generalsmuts [Summer 2005]. I dressed up as a french person, and we all did horrible teenager things like smoked (twiglets in some cases) and drank until our throats fell out. It wasn\'t big or clever. But we thought we were. James\'s House.

properties.name: Trent Park
properties.description: Posted by Generalsmuts Summer (June 1st) \'05. This is when James and Steph and John and I really became best buds, but Steph and John were having private time so James and I got chatting. It was lovely. I had short hair.

properties.name: Under the Bridge & Treasure Hunting
properties.description: Posted by Generalsmuts I found the best sailors hat washed up on the Thames beaches just here, after our picnic in Soho Square. We sat under this bridge and sang pop dittys rather badly to the people walking above us. They did clap for our (sparkling) rendition of Like a Virgin though.

properties.name: Valentine's Day
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsSteph\'s House (Which is shown as a building site here). 14th Feb, \'06. Us lonely singletons (James, Steph, Lucy and me) meet up for a booze up. James and Steph got married.

properties.name: Very Good
properties.description: Posted by GeneralsmutsEmerald Staged this picture around February or March (2006) perhaps.
